RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 55. Maiden Claiming Purse 23000. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DYNAMIC SUN stalked the pace from the two path down the backstretch then took the lead entering the final turn, drew off and won going away. EL KECZAL was unhurried around the first turn then steadily advanced moving between horses on the backstretch, tipped out to four wide at the three sixteenths pole and made a late rally. FREE DROP ROB was allowed to settle to the first turn then move between horses to be forwardly placed on the backstretch, tipped out to three wide at the three sixteenths pole and was along for the show. GUNPOWDER N' LEAD raced near the pack while saving ground around the final turn and passed tiring rivals in the stretch. I NITA WARRIOR went to the front to a clear lead for a half then was challenged into the final turn and fought gamely to mid stretch and tired. YES JACK tracked the leaders from off the rail to the quarter pole and failed to menace. SECRET RIDDLES was forwardly placed down the backstretch then moved up from three wide to engage the leader entering the final turn and was empty. FRENETIC DAY raced in the middle of the pack from off the rail but was never a threat. DADSAMUMBLER raced in the middle of the pack from the inside through the first turn then dropped back.

ENTRY.NAME: Dadsamumbler
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground, middle of pack, dropped back,

ENTRY.NAME: I Nita Warrior
ENTRY.OWNER: Reeves Jeffery Sr and Denmark Ryan

ENTRY.NAME: Gunpowder n' Lead
ENTRY.COMMENT: near back, saved ground, passed tiring rivals,

ENTRY.NAME: Yes Jack
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked leaders, off rail, failed to menace,

ENTRY.NAME: Frenetic Day
ENTRY.OWNER: Gustafson, Dawn M. and Darwin L.
ENTRY.COMMENT: middle of pack, off rail, no threat

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 2 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 87. Allowance Purse 36000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, WAIVER CLAIMING, STARTER OR TRIAL OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since November 19 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since October 19 Allowed 4 lbs. (Claiming Races Not Considered In Estimating Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TENNESSEE MOON broke well the settled off the pace and chased the leader down the backstretch, moved up to engage the leader past the quarter pole, took the lead past the three sixteenths pole, drew clear in the stretch and was kept to task late. FROSTED DIAMOND was unhurried on the inside to the three furlong marker then started to take aim on the leaders going three wide at the five sixteenths pole and kept on for the late rally and finished strong. PEQUENA TORMENTA was rushed to a clear lead and set the pace for the first half then was headed at the quarter pole and weakened. MISS LONELYHEARTS tracked the leader from the inside to the final turn, made a mild gain around the final turn but faltered in the stretch. CAVE CREEK raced in the middle of the pack from off the rail but never made a bid. FLAT OUT ROSE saved ground to no avail. SPECIAL TREASURE trailed the field while being outrun.

ENTRY.NAME: Tennessee Moon
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke well, chased leader, led 3/16, kept to task

ENTRY.NAME: Pequena Tormenta
ENTRY.COMMENT: rushed to lead, set pace, headed 1/4, weakened

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 3 5F Dirt CR: 65. Maiden Claiming Purse 38000. (INCLUDES UP TO $1,400 LTBASBF) FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SUMMERTIME PEPPERS sprinted to the lead then pulled away through the turn and proved best. TITANIUM DEAL was off the pace in the two path, chased the leader home and was second best. MALADJUSTED MISFIT pressed the pace from the inside and was along for the show. FRAN'S STAR prompted the pace from four wide early then fell back on the turn and tired. WICKED PUNCHES raced one paced throughout and was not a factor. PUPPETEER showed no early speed and remained back. HIT THE BULLSEYE was void of speed and was always back. LEXINGTON RIVER was reluctant to load, raced wide and was not a threat.

ENTRY.NAME: Summertime Peppers
ENTRY.COMMENT: sprint to lead, pulled away, best

ENTRY.NAME: Titanium Deal
ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace, chased home, second best,

ENTRY.NAME: Fran's Star
ENTRY.COMMENT: prompt pace early, fell back, tired

ENTRY.NAME: Lexington River
ENTRY.COMMENT: reluctant to load, wide trip, no threat,

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 4 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 69. Claiming Purse 13000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROLL ON OUT rushed to the lead to set all the pace, was challenged around the final turn but came again to prevail. OUT MAKING TREBLE saved ground while racing near the back down the backstretch then angled out to make a bid and moved between horses near the five sixteenths pole, tipped out to four wide into upper stretch and made a late rally. ASTERN BANKER raced off the pace in the two path through the final turn then moved in to make a rail bid in the stretch but was outfinished. LOVE A FIGHTER pressed the pace from the two path down the backstretch, engaged the leader around the final turn but weakened. CAPTAINS COVE raced six wide around the first turn then tipped in to three wide and made a middle move to be off the pace down the backstretch but lacked the late response in the drive. HULLINAHURRY raced five wide into the first turn then settled in the middle of the pack on the inside but lacked a late response. EL MIC TIESUN was allowed to settle down the backstretch then moved between horses at the three sixteenths pole and was closing but was too late. AWESOME CAJUN raced near the back, made a mild bid on the backstretch but failed to menace. WINGS OF GOLD was unhurried around the first turn and remained back. NOBLE CONNECTION stalked the pace around the first turn and slowly retreated.

ENTRY.NAME: El Mic Tiesun
ENTRY.COMMENT: allowed to settle, between 3/16, closing, too late

ENTRY.NAME: Roll On Out
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pace, challenged 2trn, came again, prevailed

ENTRY.NAME: Astern Banker
ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace, rail bid stretch, outfinished

ENTRY.NAME: Awesome Cajun
ENTRY.COMMENT: near back, mild bid, failed to menace,

ENTRY.NAME: Hullinahurry
ENTRY.COMMENT: 5w1st, middle of pack, lacked late response,

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 5 5F Dirt CR: 78. Claiming Purse 11000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since November 19 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: OVERDELIVER raced off the pace on the inside to the turn then moved out to three wide through the turn and ran down the leader to be up in the final jumps. OJITOS dueled for the lead from the three path to the quarter pole then edged away and cleared at the top of the stretch but was caught in the final jumps. WESLEYAN vied for the lead from the inside to the turn then fell back around the turn but made a rebid from the inside to be up for the third place money. DIABLO CAT had an awkward start then hopped outward and raced wide but made a late six wide rally in the stretch. CAJUN BERTI dueled for the lead from the five path to the three furlong maker and weakened. WHACUDPOSBLYGOWRNG chased the leader to the turn then made a two wide bid on the turn and flattened out. WAR SONG dueled for the lead from the inside to the quarter pole and gave way. CHICAGO CHROME dueled for the lead from the four path to the three furlong maker and dropped back.

ENTRY.NAME: Overdeliver
ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace inside, 3wturn, ran down leader, up final jumps

ENTRY.NAME: Wesleyan
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied inside, fell back, rebid inside, up show

ENTRY.NAME: Ojitos
ENTRY.COMMENT: dueled for lead, edged away, cleared, caught final jumps

ENTRY.NAME: Diablo Cat
ENTRY.COMMENT: awkward start, hopped outward, raced wide, 6wlate rally

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 6 7F Dirt CR: 78. Claiming Purse 20000. (INCLUDES UP TO $1,400 LTBASBF) FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since November 19 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since October 19 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Races Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Estimating Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GIRL THIRSTY settled on the inside down the backstretch then slipped through midway through the final turn, split horses at the sixteenths pole to prevail. BLESSED ANNA raced off the pace from between horses down the backstretch then made a three wide bid on the turn but couldn't catch the leader and was out kicked by inside rival. ANGELA'S CELERITY vied for the lead from three wide then took the lead midway down the backstretch and drew clear on the final turn but was collared in the final sixteenth and tired. SEE SASSY RUN showed brief early speed around the first turn but was overtaken near the half mile marker and fought gamely down the backstretch but tired. START WELL was unhurried to the final turn and passed tiring rivals. CRIDER CHASE pressed the pace from the two path to the three furlong marker then started to fade and was vanned off. SERIOUSLY SAM raced near the back from three wide then made a mild bid from four wide at the three furlong marker but gave way on the final turn.

ENTRY.NAME: See Sassy Run
ENTRY.OWNER: Evans Justin R and Miller Paul

ENTRY.NAME: Girl Thirsty
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled, slipped thru, split horses, prevailed

ENTRY.NAME: Blessed Anna
ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace, 3wturn, couldn't catch, out kicked

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 7 5F Dirt CR: 88. Allowance Purse 36000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since November 19 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since October 19 Allowed 4 lbs. (Claiming Races Not Considered In Es timating Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RING TWICE went to a pressured lead and was headed at the eighth pole but came again to prevail. MALIBU TOAST pressed the pace through the turn and took a brief lead at the eighth pole, fought gamely to hold the place. MISS SHIPMAN tracked the leaders to the turn then made a three or four wide bid on the turn for the late run but was not enough. EXPECT A DANCER vied for the lead from four wide to the turn then fell back slightly but came again in the stretch while fighting gamely but missed the show. FIRE VISION vied for the lead from the inside to mid turn and weakened. BIG BEAUTY showed no early speed but gave late effort in the stretch to improve position. BROKEN HEARTS BAY was void of speed while racing wide throughout and passed tired ones in the stretch. HAMAZING LACE raced in the middle of the pack from the four path, made a mild bid into the stretch and faltered. HOPESHECANRUN raced off the pace from two wide to the turn and dropped back. PSALM PRAYER broke through the gate prior to the start and was not a factor.
